duties_responsibilities.duty: Provide evidence-based medical care and develop a patient-provider relationship, promoting patient participation in wellness goals.
Work with a team to develop and implement a biopsychosocial plan of care, disease management, case management, and wellness coaching.
Manage 10-15 patients per day, providing primary care medical services including preventive, chronic, and acute care.
Participate in process improvement, quality assurance, and ongoing development of the team-based approach while leading change management.
Promote health and wellness for patients through health coaching, health risk assessment, and other health promotion strategies.

education_certification.credential: Nurse Practitioner with current Board Certification from AANP or ANCC
